<subSubSection pageId="209" pageNumber="210" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="209.[151,1437,690,2013]" pageId="209" pageNumber="210">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[704,980,1266,1293]" pageId="209" pageNumber="210">North Pacific Frostfish</emphasis>
. To 
<quantity box="[1032,1115,1267,1293]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1199999999999999" pageId="209" pageNumber="210" unit="cm" value="112.0">112 cm</quantity>
(
<quantity box="[1131,1213,1267,1294]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.12014" pageId="209" pageNumber="210" unit="in" value="44.1">44.1 in</quantity>
) SL. Kyushu-Palau Ridge and Ryukyu Islands, 
<collectingCountry box="[506,570,1303,1329]" name="Japan" pageId="209" pageNumber="210">Japan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Nakamura and Parin" box="[583,881,1303,1329]" firstAuthor="Nakamura" pageId="209" pageNumber="210" refId="ref304561" refString="Nakamura, I. &amp; Parin, N. V. (1993) FAO species catalogue. Volume 15. Snake mackerels and cutlassfishes of the world. FAO Fisheries Synopsis, No. 125, Volume 15. FAO, Rome." type="book" year="1993">Nakamura and Parin 1993</bibRefCitation>
); British Columbia and Puget Sound, Washington (
<bibRefCitation author="Peden and Hughes" box="[205,485,1339,1366]" firstAuthor="Peden" pageId="209" pageNumber="210" pagination="1 - 9" refId="ref311256" refString="Peden, A. E. &amp; Hughes, G. W. (1986) First records, confirmatory records, and range extensions of marine fishes off Canada's west coast. Canadian Field-Naturalist, 100, 1 - 9." type="journal article" year="1986">Peden and Hughes 1986</bibRefCitation>
) to Monterey Bay, central California (
<bibRefCitation author="Anderson and Cailliet" box="[925,1245,1338,1365]" firstAuthor="Anderson" pageId="209" pageNumber="210" pagination="149 - 153" refId="ref260618" refString="Anderson, M. E. &amp; Cailliet, G. M. (1975) Occurrence of the rare North Pacific frostfish, Benthodesmus elongatus pacificus Parin and Becker, 1970, in Monterey Bay, California. California Fish and Game, 61, 149 - 153." type="journal article" year="1975">Anderson and Cailliet 1975</bibRefCitation>
). Benthopelagic; depth: to 
<quantity box="[305,377,1375,1401]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.8" pageId="209" pageNumber="210" unit="m" value="380.0">380 m</quantity>
(
<quantity box="[392,484,1375,1402]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.797808" pageId="209" pageNumber="210" unit="ft" value="1246.0">1,246 ft</quantity>
) and deeper, sometimes migrating to surface; juveniles mesopelagic (
<bibRefCitation author="Nakamura and Parin" firstAuthor="Nakamura" pageId="209" pageNumber="210" refId="ref304561" refString="Nakamura, I. &amp; Parin, N. V. (1993) FAO species catalogue. Volume 15. Snake mackerels and cutlassfishes of the world. FAO Fisheries Synopsis, No. 125, Volume 15. FAO, Rome." type="book" year="1993">Nakamura and Parin 1993</bibRefCitation>
). Originally described as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Clarke, 1879)" baseAuthorityName="Clarke" baseAuthorityYear="1879" box="[807,1262,1411,1437]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Trichiuridae" genus="Benthodesmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="209" pageNumber="210" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="elongatus">
<emphasis box="[807,1087,1411,1437]" italics="true" pageId="209" pageNumber="210">Benthodesmus elongatus</emphasis>
(Clarke, 1879)
</taxonomicName>
, this form was treated as a full species by 
<bibRefCitation author="Nakamura and Parin" box="[517,837,1447,1473]" firstAuthor="Nakamura" pageId="209" pageNumber="210" refId="ref304561" refString="Nakamura, I. &amp; Parin, N. V. (1993) FAO species catalogue. Volume 15. Snake mackerels and cutlassfishes of the world. FAO Fisheries Synopsis, No. 125, Volume 15. FAO, Rome." type="book" year="1993">Nakamura and Parin (1993)</bibRefCitation>
and recognized as such by Nelson 
<emphasis box="[1251,1310,1447,1473]" italics="true" pageId="209" pageNumber="210">et al.</emphasis>
(2004); 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Parin &amp; Becker" authorityYear="1970" class="Actinopterygii" family="Trichiuridae" genus="Benthodesmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="209" pageNumber="210" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pacificus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="209" pageNumber="210">B. pacificus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in the North Pacific, whereas 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Clarke" baseAuthorityYear="1879" box="[728,870,1483,1509]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Trichiuridae" genus="Benthodesmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="209" pageNumber="210" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="elongatus">
<emphasis box="[728,870,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="209" pageNumber="210">B. elongatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in the Southern Hemisphere in the Indian, Pacific, and Atlantic Oceans. Records from British Columbia and Washington (
<bibRefCitation author="Peden and Hughes" box="[1090,1366,1519,1546]" firstAuthor="Peden" pageId="209" pageNumber="210" pagination="1 - 9" refId="ref311256" refString="Peden, A. E. &amp; Hughes, G. W. (1986) First records, confirmatory records, and range extensions of marine fishes off Canada's west coast. Canadian Field-Naturalist, 100, 1 - 9." type="journal article" year="1986">Peden and Hughes 1986</bibRefCitation>
) were reported as 
<taxonomicName authority="(Gunther, 1877)" baseAuthorityName="Gunther" baseAuthorityYear="1877" box="[329,753,1555,1581]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Trichiuridae" genus="Benthodesmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="209" pageNumber="210" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tenuis">
<emphasis box="[329,564,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="209" pageNumber="210">Benthodesmus tenuis</emphasis>
(Günther, 1877)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
